HEADWORD: melosa
<hw>melosa</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A South American herb (<spn>Madia
sativa</spn>) with sticky glandular foliage; it is a source of
<prod>madia oil</prod>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Chile tarweed, madia oil plant, <spn>Madia
sativa</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melospiza</ent>⟦br⟧
